  You are required to complete three exercises related to the following two
  regular languages. The alphabet contains three symbols: <math|a, b, c.>

  <\enumerate>
    <item><math|L<around*|(|<around*|(|<around*|(|\<epsilon\><around*|\|| a
    b|\<nobracket\>>|)><rsup|\<ast\>>c|)><rsup|\<ast\>>|)>>

    <item><math|L<around*|(|<around*|(|a<around*|\||b|)><rsup|\<ast\>>a<around*|(|b<around*|\||c|\<nobracket\>>|)><around*|(|a<around*|\||b|\|>c|)>|)>|)>>
  </enumerate>

  <with|font-series|bold|Exercise 1:> Design NFAs to recognize each of the
  above two regular languages. Is each of the NFAs designed by you also a
  DFA? [20 points]

  \;

  <with|font-series|bold|Exercise> <with|font-series|bold|2>: Convert the
  above two regular expressions to NFAs using the Thompson's Construction
  Algorithm (Algorithm 3.23 in the dragon book). Please put down the detailed
  steps and DO NOT optimize the NFAs. [40 points]

  \;

  <with|font-series|bold|Exercise 3:> Convert the NFAs in Exercise 2 to DFAs
  using the Subset Construction Algorithm (Algorithm 3.20 in the dragon
  book). Please put down the detailed steps. [40 points]

  \;
